Usually teams have a wiki to capture functional and technical information then as teams work on the stories this information becomes stale as they store the change specific information in the story itself. The information in confluence becomes outdated and updating it becomes a separate task which most teams do not spend time on keeping in mind the minimum documentation mode of Agile.

There should be a way of relating a version of a section in a page or a multiple sections in multiple pages to a story. This version then can then be made current when the story is completed. 

This way teams will have a consistent place to keep the information which is updated automatically as the work gets done. This will reduce the need to keep information in multiple places.

